The Chronicle Leonard Ncube, Victoria Falls Reporter PRESIDENT Emmerson Mnangagwa arrived in Victoria Falls on Thursday ahead of tomorrow”s official opening of the Zimbabwe Annual Mining Conference which he will preside over. President Mnangagwa was initially expected to officially open the occasion at 12 on Friday, but Chamber of Mines chief executive officer Mr Isaac Kwesu told journalists on Thursday that the programme had been altered so the Head of State speaks earlier as he has other commitments elsewhere. More to follow…